The International Telecommunications Union (ITU) will today begin a four-day 1st Digital African Week conference in Abuja. Hosted by the Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC), is expected to bring together leading specialists in the field, from top policy-makers to engineers, designers, smart city planners, government officials, regulators, standards experts, the academia among others. Executive Vice Chairman (EVC)/CEO of the NCC, Prof. Umar Garba Danbatta, said “this Conference is first of its kind and it will bring together everybody that has a role in the fast growing telecommunications industry in Africa.” FG urges support for Nigeria’s candidacy at ITU election NCC boss wants right policies to fast track digital growth in Africa Nigeria has made much progress in telecom sector – ITU Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin